    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "1 Corinthians",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 12,
        "summary": "The Holy Ghost reveals that Jesus is the Christ\u2014Spiritual gifts are present among the Saints\u2014Apostles, prophets, and miracles are found in the true Church.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "Now concerning spiritual gifts, brethren, I would not have you ignorant.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 25,
                        "end": 31
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Ye know that ye were Gentiles, carried away unto these dumb idols, even as ye were led.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0led astray.",
                        "start": 31,
                        "end": 43
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Idolatry.",
                        "start": 60,
                        "end": 65
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Wherefore I give you to understand, that no man speaking by the Spirit of God calleth Jesus accursed: and that no man can say that Jesus is the Lord, but by the Holy Ghost.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Revelation; Testimony.",
                        "start": 122,
                        "end": 125
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Lord.",
                        "start": 144,
                        "end": 148
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "John 6:44 (44, 63\u201365). TG\u00a0Holy Ghost, Mission of; Holy Ghost, Source of Testimony; Inspiration.",
                        "start": 161,
                        "end": 171
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 106,
                        "end": 110
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Now there are diversities of gifts, but the same Spirit.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0God, Gifts of; Holy Ghost, Gifts of; Holy Ghost, Mission of.",
                        "start": 29,
                        "end": 34
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And there are differences of administrations, but the same Lord.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And there are diversities of operations, but it is the same God which worketh all in all.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "But the manifestation of the Spirit is given to every man to profit withal.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 46:16 (8\u201318). TG\u00a0God, Spirit of.",
                        "start": 29,
                        "end": 35
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For to one is given by the Spirit the word of wisdom; to another the word of knowledge by the same Spirit;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 35:23.",
                        "start": 14,
                        "end": 19
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 25:7; 35:19.",
                        "start": 27,
                        "end": 33
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 89:2.",
                        "start": 38,
                        "end": 42
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Wisdom.",
                        "start": 46,
                        "end": 52
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Moro. 10:10. TG\u00a0Holy Ghost, Gifts of; Knowledge.",
                        "start": 77,
                        "end": 86
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "To another faith by the same Spirit; to another the gifts of healing by the same Spirit;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Faith.",
                        "start": 11,
                        "end": 16
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Heal.",
                        "start": 61,
                        "end": 68
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "To another the working of miracles; to another prophecy; to another discerning of spirits; to another divers kinds of tongues; to another the interpretation of tongues:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Miracle.",
                        "start": 26,
                        "end": 34
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Prophecy.",
                        "start": 47,
                        "end": 55
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Discernment, Spiritual.",
                        "start": 68,
                        "end": 78
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Language.",
                        "start": 160,
                        "end": 167
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 102,
                        "end": 108
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "But all these worketh that one and the selfsame Spirit, dividing to every man severally as he will.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For as the body is one, and hath many members, and all the members of that one body, being many, are one body: so also is Christ.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 119,
                        "end": 121
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "For by one Spirit are we all baptized into one body, whether we be Jews or Gentiles, whether we be bond or free; and have been all made to drink into one Spirit.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Church.",
                        "start": 47,
                        "end": 51
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0Greeks. Col. 3:11.",
                        "start": 75,
                        "end": 83
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0slaves. D&C 24:11; 43:20.",
                        "start": 99,
                        "end": 103
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 61,
                        "end": 66
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 93,
                        "end": 98
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "For the body is not one member, but many.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "If the foot shall say, Because I am not the hand, I am not of the body; is it therefore not of the body?",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And if the ear shall say, Because I am not the eye, I am not of the body; is it therefore not of the body?",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "If the whole body were an eye, where were the hearing? If the whole were hearing, where were the smelling?",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 18,
                        "end": 22
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 37,
                        "end": 41
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 68,
                        "end": 72
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 88,
                        "end": 92
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "But now hath God set the members every one of them in the body, as it hath pleased him.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And if they were all one member, where were the body?",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 39,
                        "end": 43
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "But now are they many members, yet but one body.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 8,
                        "end": 16
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And the eye cannot say unto the hand, I have no need of thee: nor again the head to the feet, I have no need of you.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 84:109. TG\u00a0Leadership.",
                        "start": 76,
                        "end": 80
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Nay, much more those members of the body, which seem to be more feeble, are necessary:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0weaker.",
                        "start": 59,
                        "end": 70
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And those members of the body, which we think to be less honourable, upon these we bestow more abundant honour; and our uncomely parts have more abundant comeliness.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 10,
                        "end": 17
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 129,
                        "end": 134
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "For our comely parts have no need: but God hath tempered the body together, having given more abundant honour to that part which lacked:",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 15,
                        "end": 20
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 118,
                        "end": 122
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "That there should be no schism in the body; but that the members should have the same care one for another.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Cor. 1:10 (10\u201315).",
                        "start": 86,
                        "end": 90
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 48,
                        "end": 52
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And whether one member suffer, all the members suffer with it; or one member be honoured, all the members rejoice with it.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Suffering.",
                        "start": 23,
                        "end": 29
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Compassion.",
                        "start": 47,
                        "end": 53
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Now ye are the body of Christ, and members in particular.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Head of the Church.",
                        "start": 23,
                        "end": 29
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Church Organization.",
                        "start": 35,
                        "end": 42
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And God hath set some in the church, first apostles, secondarily prophets, thirdly teachers, after that miracles, then gifts of healings, helps, governments, diversities of tongues.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Apostles.",
                        "start": 43,
                        "end": 51
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Prophets, Mission of.",
                        "start": 65,
                        "end": 73
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Teacher.",
                        "start": 83,
                        "end": 91
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Governments.",
                        "start": 145,
                        "end": 156
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Are all apostles? are all prophets? are all teachers? are all workers of miracles?",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Miracle.",
                        "start": 73,
                        "end": 81
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "type": "paper-page-number",
                        "data": 1454
                    }
                ],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 3
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 18,
                        "end": 21
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 36,
                        "end": 39
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 54,
                        "end": 57
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Have all the gifts of healing? do all speak with tongues? do all interpret?",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "But covet earnestly the best gifts: and yet shew I unto you a more excellent way.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0seek earnestly, be zealous for. D&C 46:8 (8\u20139). TG\u00a0Covet.",
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 19
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Holy Ghost, Gifts of.",
                        "start": 29,
                        "end": 34
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ether 12:11 (11\u201312, 32).",
                        "start": 67,
                        "end": 76
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            }
        ]
    }
}